<% content_for :title, "About · PriceTracker" %>
<main class="pt-page">
  <section class="pt-hero">
    <div class="container-xl">
      <div class="pt-eyebrow">About</div>
      <h1 class="pt-h1">About PriceTracker</h1>
      <p class="pt-lede">
        PriceTracker is a class project for CS 397 (Software Studio, Spring 2026)
        at Northwestern. It lets shoppers paste a product link from supported
        retailers — Amazon, Target, Walmart, Best Buy, and Lululemon — and
        watches the price over time so you know when something drops.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container-xl pt-content">
    <h2>The team</h2>
    <p>Built by students in NU CS Software Studio, Spring 2026.</p>

    <h2>The code</h2>
    <p>
      PriceTracker is open source. Browse the repository on
      <a href="https://github.com/NU-CS-Software-Studio-Spring-26/project-smart-shopping-list"
         target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Issues, bug reports, and feature requests are tracked on the project's
      <a href="https://github.com/NU-CS-Software-Studio-Spring-26/project-smart-shopping-list/issues"
         target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Issues page</a>.
    </p>
  </section>
</main>
